There are a few pastimes I love to enjoy by myself. However, if I had to pick one, it would be learning English.
I love nothing more than practicing the English language at my terraced house while enjoying a cup of coffee.
There are a variety of reasons why I fall in love with English. Firstly, I would love to travel many countries. Being profient in English enables me to converse with locals, exchange views, make friends with people from different cultures. Specifically, I would love nothing more than to visit Kyoto. To visit many of the incredible tourist attractions, as well as to enjoy artworks at Louvre Museum. Secondly, I dream of working in a prestigious multinational company. Therefore, I want to learn English to communicate effectively with my team leader and coworkers as well as to have an improved quality of life by drawing upon all of the facilities that an international company offers. In the past, I felt frustrated about learning English. I really struggled with the grammar and understanding all of the wide range of vocabulary. Even worse, I can listen and understand the questions but can't give a fully detailed response. In contrast, now I feel ecstatic and elated about English. Because I love my beloved teacher, Mr. Tung who has managed to spark my interest and motivate me to follow my dream of master the language.
That is why in the future, I will truly put my heart and soul into mastering English.

# Improved
There are several pastimes that I enjoy when I am alone. However, if I had to choose one, it would definitely be learning English.
I enjoy practicing English at my terraced house while sipping a cup of coffee. Studying in a quiet and comfortable environment helps me concentrate better and fully immerse myself in the language.
There are several reasons why I have fallen in love with English. First of all, I have a strong desire to travel to different countries in the future. Being proficient in English allows me to communicate with locals, exchange ideas, and make friends from diverse cultural backgrounds. For example, I would love to visit Kyoto and explore its breaktaking temples and traditional streets. I also dream of visiting the Louve Museum to admire its world-famouse artworks.
Secondly, I aspire to work for a prestigious multinational company. Therefore, mastering English is essential for me to communicate effectively with my team leader and colleagues. It also give me access to better career opportunities and a higher quality of life, thanks to the professional environment and benefits that international companies offer.
In the past, I often felt frustrated when learning English. I struggled with grammar and had difficulty understanding a wide range of vocabulary. What was even more discouraging was that although I could understand questions when listening, I found it hard to give detailed and confident responses. However, my feelings has completely changed. Now, I feel estatic and motivated when I study English. One of the main reasons for this transformation is my beloved teacher, Mr. Tung, who has inspired me and sparked my passion for the language. He has encouraged me to pursue my dream of mastering English.
That is why I am determined to put my heart and soul into improving my English skills in the future.
